---
title: How a Wi-Fi Talos worker joins the cluster
config:
  layout: elk
---
flowchart LR
  accTitle: Bridged Wi-Fi Talos worker architecture
  accDescr: Omni on the management NUC asks the provider on the Wi-Fi CachyOS host to create a Talos virtual machine. An ASUS media bridge presents Ethernet over Wi-Fi, the host and VM sit directly on the HomeLab VLAN, and Cilium tunnels cross-node pod traffic between node addresses.

  subgraph MANAGEMENT["MANAGEMENT"]
    direction TB
    GIT["`Git desired state
    machine class, template,
    static VM address`"]
    OMNI["`Omni on NUC
    machine lifecycle and Talos config`"]
    GIT desired@--> OMNI
  end

  subgraph LAN["HOMELAB VLAN 192.168.10.0/24"]
    direction LR
    CORE["`Wired Talos core
    control plane and GPU worker`"]
    MB["`ASUS media bridge
    proxy-STA Ethernet over Wi-Fi
    L3-aware; static VM address`"]
    DELL["`CachyOS Dell host
    br0 bridge + libvirt provider`"]
    VM["`Talos worker VM
    static 192.168.10.119
    no storage ownership`"]
    CORE coreToMb@<--> MB
    MB mbToDell@<--> DELL
    DELL dellToVm@<--> VM
  end

  subgraph PODS["KUBERNETES DATA PLANE"]
    direction TB
    ROUTES["`Cilium VXLAN tunnel
    pod traffic encapsulated
    between node IPs`"]
  end

  OMNI request@--> DELL
  CORE ownsExisting@--> ROUTES
  VM ownsDell@--> ROUTES

  classDef action fill:#fde8e8,stroke:#dc8c8c,color:#17212b
  classDef desired fill:#e1f3e8,stroke:#7bc397,color:#17212b
  classDef controller fill:#dff4f6,stroke:#70bcc4,color:#17212b
  classDef external fill:#fff3df,stroke:#d8ad55,color:#17212b
  class GIT desired
  class OMNI,DELL,VM controller
  class MB external
  class CORE,ROUTES action

  desired@{ animation: slow }
  request@{ animation: fast }
  coreToMb@{ animation: fast }
  mbToDell@{ animation: fast }
  dellToVm@{ animation: fast }
  ownsExisting@{ animation: slow }
  ownsDell@{ animation: slow }
